text:
Hello Developers. I am having an issue documented here. <https://integrate.HubSpot.com/t/is-containing-does-not-seem-to-work-when-looking-at-list-memberships/14498/5>

The short of it, anyone know how to replicate a smart module based on list membership?

I was thinking it should be {% if request.contact.list_memberships is containing 5 %} but this fails to execute.

A form was integrated for a client during a migration/setup. When the email field is filled in, as soon as you start typing you get an error "Email must be formatted correctly." It doesn't look like this is in the custom js file but I can't recall seeing this issue before. It looks like its happening on keyup instead of when they go to the next field
HubSpot form on wp or something?

I haven't seen that behavior in a HubSpot form before. It is a HubSpot form, on a HubSpot page that was migrated by HubSpot. I checked their main site (WP) to see if maybe HubSpot had just copied some code, but that form doesn't use validation the same as this nor have that message.
I would contact the migration team manager
